OL,3,CMore difficult decisions ahead for
OL,4,Cthe BBC
OL,6,GAs if the BBC's money worries weren't
OL,7,Gbad enough, Monday brought a bitter
OL,8,Gblow.
OL,10,FIt looks like the government will
OL,11,Fabandon an understanding that the
OL,12,Flicence fee will go up in line with
OL,13,Finflation next year.
OL,15,FIf this happens, there will be more
OL,16,Funpleasant decisions on programmes
OL,17,Fand services.
OL,19,FThere is simply no way that the BBC
OL,20,Fcould deal with another real terms
OL,21,Fcut by looking at overheads,
OL,22,Fefficiencies or a few niche services.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/7
