OL,3,CMore difficult decisions ahead for
OL,4,Cthe BBC
OL,6,FBeware those who hide behind anodyne
OL,7,Farguments about helping hard-pressed
OL,8,Ffamily budgets. This is the
OL,9,Fgovernment which abolished free TV
OL,10,Flicences for the over-75s.
OL,12,FFreelancers in the TV industry have
OL,13,Fsuffered from a commissioning
OL,14,Fdownturn ` a further squeeze on the
OL,15,FBBC will only make things worse.
OL,17,FMore importantly for the public, it
OL,18,Fis bound to lead to fewer programmes
OL,19,Fof quality and ambition.
OL,21,FAnd yet on this day of bad news for
OL,22,Fthe BBC came a little light.
