OL,3,CMore difficult decisions ahead for
OL,4,Cthe BBC
OL,6,FBut it has been a slow burning
OL,7,Fsuccess with the daytime audience
OL,8,Feven though it has had little
OL,9,Fpublicity. It often gets
OL,10,Fsignificantly more viewers than
OL,11,FLorraine and This Morning on ITV 1
OL,12,Fthough you would never know it from
OL,13,Fthe tabloids and celebrity mags.
OL,15,FMost of the content can hardly be
OL,16,Fcalled innovative but it has a
OL,17,Fgenuine warmth and sincerity while
OL,18,Foccasionally the content takes an
OL,19,Funexpected turn.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/7
